title.narrative: Stepping Up Universal Access: A Multi-Sectoral Partnership Response to TB/HIV

description.narrative: Lesotho - TB/HIV - Ministry of Finance of the Kingdom of Lesotho - MOF. This program has the following goals: Reduced HIV incidence by at least 75% from current baselines, by 2023. Reduced AIDS Related deaths by 50% from current baselines, by 2023. Mother to child transmission of HIV eliminated, (from 6% to less than 2%), by 2023. To reduce the overall mortality of TB by 75%. To reduce the overall incidence of TB by 50%. The objectives of this program are: To ensure that 75% of PLHIV, at risk of and affected by HIV benefit from HIV-sensitive social protection by 2023. To Fast Track Test and Treat Cascade to attain 95-95-95 targets by 2023. To achieve 95% access to combination prevention by 2023. To find 90% of all incident TB cases in the general public (NSP Objective 1) and among vulnerable populations (NSP Objective 4) and place cases notified on appropriate treatment. To ensure that at least 40% of the HIV/TB response is community-led and sustained by 2023. To find 90% of the incident drug-resistant TB cases, place all of them on appropriate treatment and successfully treat 75% of them, irrespectively of their HIV status (NSP Objective 3). To treat successfully 90% of all drug-susceptible TB patients, irrespectively of their HIV status (NSP Objective 2) and vulnerability (NSP Objective 4). To increase efficiencies and financial investments in HIV and TB programs from 60% to 90% of the NSP budget by 2023. To increase the workload capacity of the TB laboratory services to more than 67 000 Xpert MTB/RIF tests per year (NSP Objective 5) and enhance stewardship in the National TB Programme and maximize resources for the achievement of the strategic goals (NSP Objective 6). To remove Gender and Human Rights Related Barriers to service delivery, accessibility and utilization by 2023. To Eliminate Mother to Child Transmission and have 95% of children living with HIV on treatment by 2023. To ensure that Health System is people-centered, and sustainably integrates HIV, TB, and other infections by 2023
